3 ------- BANDWIDTH, TIME, DESIRE

It seems to me that to accomplish anything worthwhile requires three elements (without them i've found it very hard to succeed)

1) Bandwidth: the mental space to engage with the process of learning or mastering a skill

2) Time: time blocked off and available for learning/practice. Tip: what gets scheduled gets done

3) Desire: This is where your intention and purpose are helpful. A strong feeling or yearning to achieve something. Without this, obstacles can easily
become roadblocks that stop you in your tracks. Your desire/motivation must exceed the difficulty of challenges you face in order to achieve success



4 ------- CONFIDENCE

Confidence is forged through work

Spending focused time everyday understanding and restoring healthy feet for 50+ days so far has given you a deep understanding of foot health

A more powerful understanding than I had as a physical therapist who graduated with a 2 year masters degree and treated many patients with foot issues

You have absorbed and practiced the knowledge that has taken 5 years, many brains and lots of experience to forge

Why am I writing this? Because you are likely underestimating how powerful the wisdom you possess truly is when directed to the right people

When it comes to leading events and teaching workshops, confidence is earned through deep understanding

Deep understanding is built through experience, practice, visualization and fueled by sense of purpose in helping others

Be confident and be humble. Have strong opinions loosely held

Be open minded but know that you have a community of foot nerds supporting you and witnessing you on your journey to become an awesome event leader



5 ------- CRAFTING YOUR WORKSHOP PLAYBOOK

Create your own cheat sheet. A set of guidelines that are updated with every workshop you deliver

A checklist of things to do in preparation for, during, and after each workshop

An evolving template that you can improve over time and compare with other nerds



6 ------- DETAILS

Concrete details that reflect decisions you have made already or must now make. Write these down in your log.

- How long will your workshop/walk be? (60min or 120 min)
- When will you deliver your workshop/walk? [date/time]
- Where will it be hosted? [location]
- How much will it cost to register? [price]
- What do people receive in return for payment? [clear offering]
- How many people will attend? [aspiration/limit]
- How will people find out about the workshop/walk? [marketing/awareness]
- How will people pay you to register? [payment - cash, barter, credit card]
- What is the payment deadline to register?
- How will you communicate with attendees? [reminder/follow up method]

